Are you making your game through the QDK, or are you scripting the ASL in a text editor?  (Or both?)

You can accomplish what you want by writing some custom ASL in the description tag of the game object.  You can have a look [url=http&#58;//www&#46;axeuk&#46;com/quest/developer/documentation/script-game&#46;htm:3b0z66ed]here[/url:3b0z66ed] to check out how to do that.  Quote from there: &quot;[The description tag] overrides Quest's room descriptions by executing the script you specify here, or writing the text you specify here, rather than print Quest's default room description.&quot;

In other words, whenever you enter a room, whatever you specify to print here will show instead of what would normally be printed.
